Conclusion

Thus, fuzzy set operations like:

Union
Intersection
Complement
Difference

along with:

Cartesian product
Max-Min composition

were successfully implemented using Python.





code -

  A = {'x1':0.2, 'x2':0.5, 'x3':0.7}
B = {'x1':0.3, 'x2':0.6, 'x3':0.4}
# Union
union = {k: max(A[k], B[k]) for k in A}
# Intersection
intersection = {k: min(A[k], B[k]) for k in A}
# Complement
comp_A = {k: 1 - A[k] for k in A}
# Difference A - B
diff = {k: min(A[k], 1 - B[k]) for k in A}
print("Union:", union)
print("Intersection:", intersection)
print("Complement:", comp_A)
print("Difference:", diff)
# Cartesian product
relation = {(a, b): min(A[a], B[b]) for a in A for b in B}
print("Relation:", relation)

